3 WHEREAS, Principal Wax earned a bachelor of science degree in business
4 administration with a minor in leadership development from Louisiana State University; he
5 pursued a career in education through alternative certification and received a master of
6 education in educational leadership from Southeastern Louisiana University; and
7 WHEREAS, Principal Wax is a member of the Louisiana Association of Principals
8 and vice president of the Livingston Parish Principals Association; he served four years as
9 president of Mighty Moms, which is a nonprofit that "nurtures hungry students to success";
10 and
11 WHEREAS, outside of school, Principal Wax serves as a church deacon, and he is
12 a married father of three children; and
13 WHEREAS, Denham Springs Junior High School Principal Justin Wax is a dedicated
14 advocate of students and their education, and he is most deserving of the highest recognition
15 for his outstanding service.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
17 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Justin Wax for being named the 2026
18 Principal of the Year in Louisiana and does hereby extend enduring appreciation for his
19 contributions to students in Louisiana.
